//A fixed-bound subarray of nums is a subarray that satisfies the following conditions:
//The minimum value in the subarray is equal to minK.
//The maximum value in the subarray is equal to maxK.
//Return the number of fixed-bound subarrays.
//A subarray is a contiguous part of an array.
//
//Example 1:
//Input: nums = [1,3,5,2,7,5], minK = 1, maxK = 5
//Output: 2
//Explanation: The fixed-bound subarrays are [1,3,5] and [1,3,5,2].
//Example 2:
//Input: nums = [1,1,1,1], minK = 1, maxK = 1
//Output: 10
//Explanation: Every subarray of nums is a fixed-bound subarray. There are 10 possible subarrays.

//Constraints:

// .JS

    const countNum = nums.length;

        if (nums[i] < minK || nums[i] > maxK) boundPoint = i;
        if (nums[i] == minK) minPoint = i;
        if (nums[i] == maxK) maxPoint = i;

        let countPossibleSubArr = Math.min(minPoint, maxPoint) - boundPoint;  //

        if (countPossibleSubArr > 0) totalSubArr += countPossibleSubArr;
    }
    return totalSubArr;
};

     */
    function countSubarrays(array $nums, int $minK, int $maxK): int
    {
        $numsCount = count($nums);
        if (min($nums) > $minK && max($nums) < $maxK) return 0;
        $boundPoint = -1;
        $minPoint = -1;
        $maxPoint = -1;
        $countTotalSubarrays = 0;
        for ($i = 0; $i < $numsCount; $i++) {
            if ($nums[$i] < $minK || $nums[$i] > $maxK) $boundPoint = $i;
            if ($nums[$i] === $minK) $minPoint = $i;
            if ($nums[$i] === $maxK) $maxPoint = $i;
            $countSubarrays = min($minPoint, $maxPoint) - $boundPoint;
            if ($countSubarrays > 0) $countTotalSubarrays += $countSubarrays;
        }
        return $countTotalSubarrays;
    }
